OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Bob Piper
OL,5,F"There were so many wireless sets in
OL,6,Fthat small area. We had an officer
OL,7,Fthere and we had to keep the
OL,8,Fcommunication open. We had a set
OL,9,Fprocedure. You didn't give names or
OL,10,Funits. We had to teach the officers
OL,11,Fand I remember teaching a doctor and
OL,12,Fwhen he first used it he switched it
OL,13,Fon and froze.
OL,15,F"He said 'I can do an operation but
OL,16,Fthis frightens me.' I saw that doctor
OL,17,Fand he had repaired a chap's jaw."
OL,19,FMr Piper served through Belgium,
OL,20,FHolland and Germany.
